<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836094>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Cerantichir enderleini Hennig, 1937, male, dorsal view (A); Eoneria blanchardi Aczél, 1951, female, dorsal view (B); Glyphidops durus (Cresson, 1926), female, dorsal view (C), and male, abdomen (D); Glyphidops filosus (Fabricius 1805), male, head (E); Glyphidops flavifrons (Bigot, 1886), female, abdomen (F), and male, dorsal (G); Nerius plurivittatus Bigot, 1886, male, dorsal (H); Odontoloxozus longicornis (Coquillett, 1904), male, lateral (I). Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836094/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836114>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Eoneria ramirezi sp. nov.: male lateral (A) and dorsal (B), female lateral (C) and dorsal (D). Scale bar= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836114/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Habitus in lateral view. Cerantichir enderleini Hennig, 1937, male (A) and female (B); Eoneria blanchardi Aczél, 1951, female (C); Glyphidops durus (Cresson, 1926), male (D) and female (E); Glyphidops filosus (Fabricius 1805), male (F) and female (G). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836102>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cerantichir mexicana sp. nov.: male lateral (A) and dorsal (B), female lateral (C) and dorsal (D). Scale bar= 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836102/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836108>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Cerantichir mexicana sp. nov.: male lateral head (A), male antenna (B), male dorsal head (C), male terminalia dorsal (D) and lateral (E), ovipositor dorsal (F) and lateral (G). Scale bar= 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836108/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7836112>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus in lateral view. Glyphidops flavifrons (Bigot, 1886), male (A) and female (B); Nerius plurivittatus Bigot, 1886, male (C) and female (D); and Odontoloxozus longicornis (Coquillett, 1904), male (E) and female (F). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7836112/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

